		<h1>FRANCE</h1>
		<p>
			<strong>France</strong>, officially the French Republic, is a country in Western Europe known for its rich history, culture, and global influence. Bordered by Belgium and Luxembourg to the northeast, Germany, Switzerland, and Italy to the east, and Spain and Andorra to the south, France is strategically located, connecting the Atlantic Ocean to the Mediterranean Sea. It also has overseas territories around the globe, extending its reach beyond Europe. Paris, the capital and largest city, is a global hub for art, fashion, and gastronomy, famous for landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower, the Louvre Museum, and the Notre-Dame Cathedral. Other major cities include Marseille, Lyon, and Bordeaux, each contributing to the country's economic and cultural diversity. With a population of approximately 68 million people, France is one of the most populous nations in Europe. The country has a long history of innovation and leadership, from the Enlightenment and the French Revolution to its role as a founding member of the European Union and NATO. Known as the birthplace of modern democracy and human rights, France continues to be a global center for science, culture, and diplomacy, attracting millions of visitors each year who come to experience its history, cuisine, and vibrant way of life.
		</p>

